# infra/.gitignore — Terraform (deny-by-default / allowlist)
#
# SECURITY MODEL: ignore EVERYTHING in this directory, then re-include only the
# handful of safe, human-reviewable files below. Anything new — a state file, a
# *.tfvars, a service-account key, a crash log — is excluded automatically
# because it was never re-included. The default is "do not commit."
#
# NOTE: gitignore has NO inline comments. Every pattern is on its own line;
# a trailing "# ..." would become part of the pattern and silently break it.

# 1) Ignore everything in infra/ by default.
*

# 2) Re-include ONLY safe, non-sensitive source-of-truth files.
# this file itself
!.gitignore
# docs
!README.md
# main.tf / variables.tf / outputs.tf — config only, no secrets
!*.tf
# provider checksums; safe + recommended to commit
!.terraform.lock.hcl
# sanitized `terraform apply` proof (bonus artifact)
!apply-output.txt

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DELIBERATELY NEVER RE-INCLUDED (kept ignored by the `*` above). Listed so the
# intent is explicit and a reviewer can confirm nothing sensitive slips in:
#
#   terraform.tfstate, *.tfstate, *.tfstate.*   -> may embed resource data/secrets
#   *.tfvars, *.tfvars.json, *.auto.tfvars*     -> may hold project IDs / secrets
#   .terraform/                                 -> downloaded provider binaries
#   .terraform.tfstate.lock.info                -> local state lock
#   *.tfplan                                    -> binary plan can embed secrets
#   crash.log, crash.*.log                      -> may dump state on panic
#   *.json, *.pem, *.key, *-sa.json, *-key.json -> credentials / SA keys
#   override.tf, *_override.tf(.json)           -> local-only overrides
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
